news.title: Pune: Over one lakh property tax amnesty scheme beneficiaries are defaulters again
news.para: The civic administration announced a discount for nearly 2.5 lakh taxpayers in the amnesty scheme in the financial year 2020-21 and for 66,454 delinquent property owners in 2021-22 to recover outstanding taxes.

news.title: NGT panel spots green compliance gaps at ACC cement plant in Himachal Pradesh
news.para: The committee observed dust emissions from clinker, ash, and cement silos, as well as inadequate measures to prevent accidental discharges, despite directives from the HPSPCB.

news.title: Odisha RERA orders 'arbitrary', allege developers
news.para: ORERA recently heard a case suo motu regarding a real estate project in Phulnakhara, and passed an order stating that the realtor cannot proceed with further bookings until the completed units are handed over to the allottees.

news.title: Residents of 32 societies in Noida protest against registry delay
news.para: The protest highlighted the residents' frustration over the delay in pending registries. They also demanded the implementation of the original Amitabh Kant Committee report and the chief minister's intervention on the matter.

news.title: Dharwad: Over 18,000 construction workers benefit from Shramik Sanjeevini Yojana
news.para: The unit is run through agencies on a contract basis under the Karnataka Building and Other Construction Workers Welfare Board.

news.title: Visakhapatnam: VMRDA readies maps for zonal development plans
news.para: The primary goal of these maps is to serve as a foundation for developing the master plan and zonal development plans for the study area.

news.title: About 1,000 e-khata kiosks to be launched in Bengaluru
news.para: BBMP will be setting up kiosks and providing tech to make it happen, said Munish Moudgil, special commissioner (revenue).

news.title: Signature Global trims net debt 29% to Rs 720 crore in Q3 FY25
news.para: In its latest operational update, Signature Global mentioned that the net debt has come down 38 per cent to Rs 720 crore as on December 31, 2024 from Rs 1,160 crore at the end of the 2023-24 financial year.

news.title: NCLT recalls insolvency order against Logix Infrastructure
news.para: ​NCLT said "there is a nexus and connection" between its financial creditor Experts Realty Professionals whose plea for insolvency was initiated against Logix Infrastructure.

news.title: Builder fails to repair fault; 700 families left without power in Gurugram
news.para: The disconnection occurred at the 33kV switching station at 6pm on Friday and was only restored at 5pm on Saturday, with residents claiming no prior notice was given to them.

news.title: DLF Cyber City Developers' rental income rises 10% to nearly Rs 1,200 crore in Q3 FY25
news.para: The DCCDL, which holds bulk of the rent-yielding assets of DLF Group, has an operational rental portfolio of 40.4 million square feet, of which 36.4 million square feet area is office space and 4 million square feet retail real estate.

news.title: In HC, Panaji smart city blames climate change for delays
news.para: In 2024, Goa surpassed the average seasonal rainfall mark, logging 3,091 mm as of Aug 1, according to IMD. This was a departure of 54.7% from normal rainfall levels, IPSCDL said.

news.title: Lucknow development body gives NOCs to 14, nod to 30 maps
news.para: LDA vice-chairman Prathamesh Kumar reviewed cases where many applicants had long-pending issues. Sangeeta Soni from Aishbagh waited two months for NOCs from multiple departments.

news.title: Pressure mounts on Coimbatore corporation to withdraw drone survey
news.para: The councillors of these parties walked out of the corporation council meeting alleging that the drone-based survey had led to erroneous and inflated tax assessments.

news.title: Anamudi Real Estates acquires land worth Rs 80.83 crore in Mumbai
news.para: The acquisition incurred a stamp duty payment of Rs 4.85 crore. The land also includes a built-up area comprising a basement, a ground floor, and two upper floors.

news.title: Chandigarh administration's court may decide on property tax rates now
news.para: In the past, there were several instances where the Chandigarh administration turned down the MC's plea and passed its own order by reversing the MC's approval.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body house rejects proposal to hike property tax
news.para: The issue was presented in the MC house as mayor Babla allowed the table agenda, proposing increase in property tax in both commercial and residential segments.

news.title: Roads, walls among 80 illegal structures demolished in demolition drive in Gurugram
news.para: Two unauthorized ramps and a gym were demolished at Idea Cosmic Plaza and two offices sealed. Officials, including DTP (enforcement) Amit Madholia and junior engineer Naveen, oversaw the drive.

news.title: Kerala budget 2025-26: Metro rail projects in three cities to get boost
news.para: In his budget speech, the Minister said the existing Kochi Metro line would be extended to more areas in the city, and the proposed Metro projects in Kozhikode and Thiruvananthapuram would become a reality soon.

news.title: Rajasthan Housing Board earns Rs 155.62 crore by selling premium properties
news.para: "We managed to sell 44 out of the 60-odd properties listed in the auction. All these are of premium categories. This shows people have faith in RHB even in premium categories," said housing commissioner Dr Rashmi Sharma.
